  "text": "Define T (G) as the set of all directed spanning trees for a graph G. As [CITATION_1] noted, there is a one-to-one correspondence between spanning trees of G x and labeled dependency graphs of x, i.e., T (G x ) is exactly the set of all possible projective and non-projective dependency graphs for sentence x. Throughout the rest of this paper, we will refer to any T ∈ T (G x ) as a valid dependency graph for a sentence x. Thus, by definition, every valid dependency graph must be a tree.",
